{
  "texts": [
    "The balsam woolly adelgid, for example, cannot endure a winter cold of -34 degrees Celsius.",
    "If this value is not attained as a result of climate change, the length and intensity of epidemics will rise [57].",
    "The impact on forests may outweigh the physical impacts of climate change, such as drought.",
    "There is evidence that insects are already adjusting in the Canadian Boreal Shield.",
    "The time of the spruce bud worm life-cycle, for example, has been seen to alter by 3-7 days during the last 25 years [58]."
  ]
}